Hot Headed for Two-Week Low as Migdal Cuts Shares to ‘Hold’

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-05T09:59:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/hot-headed-for-two-week-low-as-migdal-cuts-shares-to-hold-.html
Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT) 
headed for the lowest close in more than two weeks after Migdal
Capital Markets Ltd. cut the cable and telecommunications
company to “hold,” citing changes in exit-fee regulation.  The shares fell as much as 1.4 percent to 61.82 shekels.
They declined 0.8 percent to 62.16 shekels, the lowest close May
18, at 12:07 p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  The shares were cut from "buy."  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
